): right conjunctival appendage with two spines, longer apically, beset with small tubercles, left conjunctival with two lobes (Figure 9I), right paramere long and slender, with gently curving apex (Figure 9H), left paramere roughly triangular with broad apex (Figure 9I,H), vesica looping, very slender, with more than four coils (Figure 9H).
